text: Trying out all the coffee spots in the Cecil area. This spot gets an average rating as there’s definitely better coffee in the area. Iced americano costs $6, and the beans tasted a tad weird. Service from the female barista could definitely be improved. Open seating area but gets a bit warm overtime, not the most conducive if you need to get work done.
I’m a frequent visitor for this cafe. It has wonderful staff serving you. And the coffee is excellent.

Chill atmosphere and lovely service staff who always make you feel welcomed. Their lattes aren’t the best, it’s really acidic. I think the issue is with the type of beans used. Their oat latte has gotten a lot better ever since they switched to Oatside milk.
Nice coffee and very reasonable priced breakfast and lunch sandwiches sets. Open space coffee place for coffee break, casual discussion or catch up with friends.
You can certainly get better coffee nearby. Also, the female service staff's attitude has lots of room for improvement
